<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
Body ~ 8.67 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Head</emphasis>
: Antenna ≥ 37-segmented, apically broken. Face width ~ 1.46 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than its height (1.02:0.70) Width of anterior ocellus ~ 0.96 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than POL. Eyes bulged and without interommatidial setae; median width of eye about ~ 0.90 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than median width of gena in lateral view (0.44:0.49). Clypeus ~ 2.61 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than its height (0.60:0.23). Malar space 0.84 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than basal width of mandible. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Mesosoma</emphasis>
: Notauli anteriorly weakly impressed and absent posteriorly. Scutellar sulcus weakly impressed, medially shallow, laterally relatively deep, without crenula. Pronotum entirely smooth. Propodeum ~ 0.44 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than its median width (0.57:1.30); median longitudinal furrow present, elongate isosceles trapezoid, anteriorly opened posteriorly closed by nucha, anterior width ~ 0.33 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than maximum width (0.04:0.12). 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Legs</emphasis>
: Basal spur on mid tibia ~ 0.64 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than length of basitarsus (0.47:0.74). Basal spur on hind tibia ~ 0.50 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than length of basitarsus (0.68:1.37). 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Wings</emphasis>
: Fore wing (RS+M)a vein present; second submarginal cell trapezoid, ~ 3.01 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than height (1.66:0.55); 1r absent; 3r absent; 3RSb evenly curved; stigma about ~ 4.42 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide medially (2.08:0.47). Hind wing 2r-m absent; 2-1A absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Metasoma</emphasis>
: T1 ~ 1.63 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than its posterior width (1.19:0.73), anterior width ~ 0.63 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than posterior width (0.46:0.73), dorsally isosceles trapezoid; Y-shaped suture partially developed anteriorly, absent posteriorly. T2 nearly trapezoid, ~ 0.42 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than its posterior width (0.44:1.06), with curved posterior margin. Hypopygium with median fold. Ovipositor sheath slightly downcurved, ~ 1.03 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than length of hind tibia (2.92:2.81), evenly setose except for base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="color">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Color.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Head and mesosoma mostly black, metasoma mostly orange and black apically. Legs black or dark brown except for fore tarsus. Fore wing with two bands; stigma pale at apical two thirds.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Named in honor of Mr Yves Braet who provided specimens collected in French Guiana for this study.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
